Recently a hard drive went out on my main home VM Server. It was in a RAID, so there was no data loss. But as I had to shut everything down to replace hardware (no hot swap&hellip;), it makes me think about also maintaining the software stack for the lab.
Currently I have two physical systems that are libvirt/KVM hosts for my virtual machines, including the main firewall and fileserver.

